-- Jain Says Burden Should Be Taken Off Central Bankers’ Shoulders
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 2013-01-25T14:23:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-25/jain-says-burden-should-be-taken-off-central-bankers-shoulders.html
Deutsche Bank AG (DBK)  co-Chief Executive
Anshu Jain said pressure should be taken away from central banks
to deal with the financial crisis.  “We’ve got to take the burden off our central bankers
shoulders and really governments and business leaders need to
pick up that slack,” Jain said on a panel in Davos, Switzerland
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Comfort in Frankfurt at 
